t: A Psalm or Song for the sabbath day.
It*p is a good thing to give thanks unto the Lord,*s and to sing praises unto thy name, O most High:
To*p shew forth thy lovingkindness in the morning, and thy faithfulness every night,
Upon*p an instrument of ten strings, and upon the psaltery; upon the harp with a solemn sound.
For*p thou, Lord,*s hast made me glad through thy work: I will triumph in the works of thy hands.
O*p Lord,*s how great are thy works! and thy thoughts are very deep.
A*p brutish man knoweth not; neither doth a fool understand this.
When*p the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish; it is that they shall be destroyed for ever:
But*p thou, Lord,*s art most high for evermore.
For,*p lo, thine enemies, O Lord,*s for, lo, thine enemies shall perish; all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.
But*p my horn shalt thou exalt like the horn of an unicorn: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.
Mine*p eye also shall see my desire on mine enemies, and mine ears shall hear my desire of the wicked that rise up against me.
The*p righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.
Those*p that be planted in the house of the Lord*s shall flourish in the courts of our God.
They*p shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be fat and flourishing;
To*p shew that the Lord*s is upright: he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
